channel.title: How to fix this Pi error
channel.description:
Hey guys, I added something to my client.java and got this error.
[code]src\server\model\players\Client.java:673: cannot find symbol symbol : method isInCwWait(server.model.players.Client) location: class server.model.minigames.CastleWars if (CastleWars.isInCwWait(this)) { ^ src\server\model\players\Client.java:674: non-static method leaveWaitingRoom(ser ver.model.players.Client) cannot be referenced from a static context CastleWars.leaveWaitingRoom(this); ^ src\server\model\players\Client.java:676: cannot find symbol symbol : method isInCw(server.model.players.Client) location: class server.model.minigames.CastleWars if (CastleWars.isInCw(this)) { ^ src\server\model\players\Client.java:677: cannot find symbol symbol : method removePlayerFromCw(server.model.players.Client) location: class server.model.minigames.CastleWars CastleWars.removePlayerFromCw(this); ^ Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 4 errors Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
I imported CastleWars by importing this,
[code]import server.model.minigames.CastleWars;[/code]
But still get the error, how do I make it recognize it? I looked in the common compiler errors, but I just don't get it :(
